results.name: Number of semistandard Young tableaux whose entries are the prime indices of n.
comment: Number of ways to fill a Young diagram with the prime indices of n such that all rows are weakly increasing and all columns are strictly increasing.
A prime index of n is a number m such that prime(m) divides n. The multiset of prime indices of n is row n of A112798.
Is this a duplicate of A339887? - _R. J. Mathar_, Feb 03 2021
